<section class="pie-clearfix" id="index">
  <section id="plans">
    {% for product in collections.frontpage.products limit: 1 %}
      <hgroup>
        <ul>
          <li><span class="check">Share <span class="compare">10 files</span> <strong>unlimited files</strong> a day</span></li>
          <li><span class="check">Upload files up to <span class="compare">25MB</span> <strong>500MB</strong></span></li>
          <li><span class="check">Share links with <span class="compare">our</span> <strong>your own domain</strong></span></li>
        </ul>
      </hgroup>

      <form action="/cart/add" method="post">
        <fieldset>
          <div>
            {% for variant in product.variants %}
              {% if variant.available && variant.sku != 'CLPRO01' %}
                {% capture id %}pro-{{ variant.title | replace: ' ', '-' }}{% endcapture %}
                <label><input {% if forloop.first %}checked {% endif %}id="{{ id }}" name="id" type="radio" value="{{ variant.id }}" /> {{ variant.title | escape }}&thinsp;&mdash;&thinsp;{% if variant.compare_at_price %}<span class="compare">{{ variant.compare_at_price | money }}</span> {% endif %}{{ variant.price | money }}</label>
              {% endif %}
            {% endfor %}
          </div>
        </fieldset>

        {% if variant.available && variant.sku == 'CLPRO01' %}
          <p>
            <small>Have commitment issues? We also offer <a href="#">1 month for $5</a>.</small>
          </p>
        {% endif %}

        <p>
          <input class="green" type="submit" value="Get CloudApp Pro" />
        </p>
      </form>

      <script>
        (function($) {
          $(function() {
            var hash = window.location.hash.replace(/#/, '');
            $("#pro-" + hash).attr("checked", "checked");
          });
        }(jQuery));
      </script>
    {% endfor %}
  </section>

  <section id="faqs">
    <div class="pie-clearfix row">
      <section class="column">
        <dt>How long are your contracts?</dt>

        <dd>
          CloudApp Pro is a pay-as-you-go service. Just like iTunes gift cards you buy months up front. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.
        </dd>
      </section>

      <section class="column">
        <dt>How do I sign up?</dt>

        <dd>
          You start with a free trial! We don't collect your credit card until your trial is over and you're ready to sign up. You can upgrade from your trial to a paid account in the Billing Details area of your site manager once you determine there's a fit.
        </dd>
      </section>

      <section class="column">
        <dt>How do I cancel service?</dt>

        <dd>

          Right next to the button you used to sign up. Canceling Squarespace is an instantaneous and no questions asked process. It's done online right from your site manager.
        </dd>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="pie-clearfix row">
      <section class="column">
        <dt>What is meant by unlimited?</dt>

        <dd>
          Squarespace's Advanced and Business packages do not have resource limits for normal usage. As per our Terms of Service, sites can not exist for the sole purpose of file sharing. Further, files uploaded to Squarespace can currently be a maximum of 20MB in size.
        </dd>
      </section>

      <section class="column">
        <dt>How do I sign up?</dt>

        <dd>
          You start with a free trial! We don't collect your credit card until your trial is over and you're ready to sign up. You can upgrade from your trial to a paid account in the Billing Details area of your site manager once you determine there's a fit.
        </dd>
      </section>

      <section class="column">
        <dt>Why isn't CloudApp entirely free?</dt>

        <dd>
          Squarespace provides a premium, time saving service and charges for it. We believe in a direct and honest relationship with our customers. Because we charge for our service and have a stable business model, we don't need to make decisions later on that would compromise our integrity in order to make money from our users.
        </dd>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</section>
